retweeted_text: I'm thrilled the Utah Navajo Water Rights Settlement Act passed the U.S. Senate and look forward to House consideration. It creates clean drinking water projects for our Navajo friends and certainty for Utah's future water needs. My sincere thanks to @SenatorRomney and @NNPrezNez https://t.co/qZ4yvOWxlh

full_text: This bill provides access to water and wastewater facilities for the Navajo Nation, and long-needed water infrastructure. Led by @RepRobBishop and @RepJohnCurtis, I urge the House to pass this without delay, so we can keep the federal government's promise to the Navajo Nation.

We have adjusted requirements to test for COVID-19. As of today, if you have any of the following six symptoms, you should seek testing: 
1) fever
2) cough
3) shortness of breath
4) sore throat
5) muscle aches
6) loss of taste or smell

full_text: The #GoldenSpike was 5 5/8 inches long, weighed 14.03 oz, and was made of 17.6 carat gold. It was driven into a tie made out of polished California laurel. The spike and tie were immediately removed and replaced with a pine tie and iron spikes to prevent theft. #Spike150 https://t.co/9RQGFxIvT4

Today I joined @MarcoRubio, @SenatorRomney and @RepAnnWagner in introducing the #NewParentsAct, a fiscally responsible paid family leave option.

Families are forced to choose between their financial well-being and the well-being of their child. Thatâ€™s wrong. Letâ€™s fix it. https://t.co/3gLfILuYIL
